01/05/2003
DUBROVNIK, Croatia -- NATO's Air Traffic Management Committee (NATMC) opened a three-day plenary session in the Adriatic town of Dubrovnik on Wednesday (30 April).
Deputy Defence Minister Jelena Grcic-Polic said the forum would provide Croatia an opportunity to present its achievements in management of air space and co-operation with NATO partners.
The meeting will also tackle issues related to international efforts against terrorism.
Croatia has participated in NATCM forums since joining the Partnership for Peace programme in May 2000.
(HINA - 30/04/03)
